data.description:
1. BTC broke $104,000 in the short term, and the cryptocurrency market rose generally;
2. SEC reached a settlement agreement with Ripple, and Ripple will pay a fine of $50 million;
3. Coinbase's total revenue in the first quarter was $2.03 billion, which was lower than analysts' expectations;
4. The founder of Celsius was sentenced to 12 years in prison for crypto fraud and confiscated $48 million and multiple properties;
5. Stablecoin legislation encountered obstacles in the Senate, and Democratic lawmakers pointed out that TRUMP coin activities were corrupt;
6. Meta once again considered integrating stablecoins to reduce payment costs after selling the Diem project;
7. Doodles: DOOD airdrop will be launched at 21:05 tonight, without manual application;
8. Kanye West retweeted a tweet with a Meme coin contract early this morning, and 2 investors FOMO bought and suffered a halving loss;
9. Trump seeks to increase taxes on the rich with an annual income of more than $2.5 million;
10. Trump: Talking to Fed Chairman Powell is like "playing the lute to a cow".
